history.content:
Hey! Picking your first upper div is very exciting! A lot of people choose cs 170 to go alongside 61c, since its pset based and 61c is project based, plus is a really important course for a cs major and helps with interviews!

Another option is data 100 (especially if you've taken data 8 and enjoyed it!) 
CS 188 is a good one if you're interested in AI
CS 160 is also good if you're interested in user interface and design!
Lots of great courses to choose!

children.subject:
I did this, along with Math 53 and a breadth; was a very heavy semester, but is manageable so long as you start everything early. 

If you do take 61C and 170 concurrently, make sure your other classes are as light as possible.
My other 2 classes should be an easy workload; do you think there's anything that would be helpful to do over summer to prepare for either 61C/170 in anticipation of the heavy semester?
Does anyone have feedback/advice on doing 61C + 170 concurrently?

history.content: I'll be taking 61c in fall 2018 and am considering taking an upper div alongside it, but haven't taken any upper divs and am not sure which ones would be the most manageable time/stress/workload wise. I know it also depends on what subjects you're most interested in but any input on upper divs + taking upper divs alongside 61c would be greatly appreciated!
